chool system, with rising poverty, large numbers of recent immigrants, and constant pressure from an assortment of special interest groups. While many school systems facing similar developments have experienced a drop in performance, Fairfax students continue to raise their achievement. Daniel L. Duke reveals the keys to Fairfax's remarkable track record.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aSchool management and organizationzVirginiazFairfax CountyvCase studies. 0aSuburban schoolszVirginiazFairfax CountyvCase studies. 4aEducation : Education. 4aEducation : Educational Administration. 4aPolitics and Law : Leadership Studies. 7aEDUCATION / Leadership.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791482988423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791482988/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles